{"tid":879598,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"矽谷精英育兒共識：唔好畀細路掂手機電腦","createTime":"2018-10-28T05:53:09.000Z","updateTime":"2018-10-29T10:24:39.000Z","uid":138409,"like":208,"dislike":8,"uniUserReply":51,"replies":[{"pid":"75867f2c5eb11a9775dd9eb8bfe1987faa55f904","tid":879598,"uid":138409,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-28T05:53:09.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/26/style/phones-children-silicon-valley.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2018%2F10%2F26%2Fstyle%2Fphones-children-silicon-valley.html&d=IT0WKWL4evWOYlI9S0Ou9EjIoeaDRyeQRMy%2FzT52C%2Fo%3D&h=cbffd90e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/26/style/phones-children-silicon-valley.html</a><br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: gold;\">有啲父母淨係搭長途車/機嘅時候先畀細路玩手機</span><br />\n／／Ms. Stecher, 37, and her husband, Rushabh Doshi, researched screen time and came to a simple conclusion: they wanted almost none of it in their house. Their daughters, ages 5 and 3, have no screen time &ldquo;budget,&rdquo; no regular hours they are allowed to be on screens. <span style=\"color: red;\">The only time a screen can be used is during the travel portion of a long car ride (the four-hour drive to Tahoe counts) or during a plane trip.</span>／／<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: gold;\">有啲直情上到高中先畀仔女用手提電話</span><br />\n／／Ms. Chavarria did not let her children have cellphones until high school, and even now bans phone use in the car and severely limits it at home.／／<br />\n[...]<br />\n// He [Chris Anderson] has five children and 12 tech rules. They include: <span style=\"color: red;\">no phones until the summer before high school</span>, no screens in bedrooms, network-level content blocking, no social media until age 13, no iPads at all and screen time schedules enforced by Google Wifi that he controls from his phone.//<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: gold;\">Steve Jobs都唔畀自己仔女掂iPad</span><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n// Tim Cook, the C.E.O. of Apple, said earlier this year that he would not let his nephew join social networks. Bill Gates banned cellphones until his children were teenagers, and Melinda Gates wrote that she wished they had waited even longer. <span style=\"color: red;\">Steve Jobs would not let his young children near iPads.</span>//<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: gold;\">手機基本上接近可卡因，難以控制<br />\n</span>／／<span style=\"color: red;\">&ldquo;On the scale between candy and crack cocaine, it&rsquo;s closer to crack cocaine,&rdquo; Mr. Anderson said of screens.<br />\nTechnologists building these products and writers observing the tech revolution were na&iuml;ve, he said.<br />\n&ldquo;We thought we could control it,&rdquo; Mr. Anderson said. &ldquo;And this is beyond our power to control. This is going straight to the pleasure centers of the developing brain. This is beyond our capacity as regular parents to understand.&rdquo;</span>／／"},{"pid":"b0a4306e10b42e194703d8dfcdf663ef182c8cef","tid":879598,"uid":138409,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-28T05:57:20.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"4ce1169f305310ab243aba60e6b76c53b3b5d351","tid":879598,"uid":138409,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-28T05:58:43.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"6b5d7750afbc0d4753fa269ef896294cfe943105","tid":879598,"uid":138409,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-28T06:01:34.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"41c9013305d4e7d954b1f1912a506e817c86a7b9","tid":879598,"uid":19979,"like":110,"dislike":0,"score":110,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-28T06:03:32.000Z","msg":"網絡遊戲策劃師：為什麼我的兒子不沉迷網絡遊戲？<br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/bkiaxS\" target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/bkiaxS</a>"},{"pid":"6ef04e85679553e8eb6b4ac994b3236ef057eb02","tid":879598,"uid":19552,"like":56,"dislike":2,"score":